    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-06-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="171"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d171">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/6–3050: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting Political Adviser in Japan</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sebald</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-06-30">June 30,
                            1950</date>.<lb/>[Received June 30—8:05 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>688. Had brief telephone conversation with Muccio at 1730 in which he spoke of
                    desperate and rapidly deteriorating situation. He said he had spent most of
                    night and practically all day with top Koreans and <pb facs="0275" n="255"
                        xml:id="pg_255"/> key members National Assembly and feels he can hold them
                    in line a little longer. Danger, however, is that they might soon panic. He
                    strongly urged all out effort before situation out of hand.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d171fn1">At 6: 50 a. m. (<gloss target="#t_EDT1">EDT</gloss>), a
                        teletype conference had been held with <gloss target="#t_HQ1">HQ</gloss>,
                            <gloss target="#t_FEC1">FEC</gloss> in Tokyo by officers of <gloss
                            target="#t_G21">G–2</gloss> in Washington along with officials of the
                        Department of State and other agencies (<gloss target="#t_DA1">DA</gloss>
                        TT–3441). The Tokyo conferees reported that the <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                            >ROK</gloss> army had suffered 60 percent casualties, was reduced to a
                        strength of 30,000 as against 100,000 North Koreans, and was low in morale;
                        they also reported that the civilian population was very pessimistic and
                        that, the Government was in a disorganized state (795.00/8–2550).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Sebald</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
